---
// "Pace lives inside this Mac" hero. A near-full-bleed faux-macOS
// desktop frame becomes the showpiece: visitors see Pace's actual
// menu-bar capsule + cursor + plan-then-execute response bubble
// inside a recognisable Mac scene, not floating in a void.
//
// Nothing here is photographic — the whole desktop is composed in
// HTML + CSS so it's pin-sharp on every screen, weighs almost
// nothing, and stays editable in the same diff as the copy.
//
// Loop drives three states (idle → asked → answered) on a 14s cycle
// so a visitor lingering long enough sees the full Pace turn play
// out twice without scrolling. Reduced-motion users see the final
// frame statically.
---

<section class="px-6 pt-16 md:pt-20 pb-10">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Editorial hero — first-person voice, single italic accent
         in the headline, no rounded badge, no centered subhead
         block. Long line of text reads like an essay opener, not
         a SaaS landing page. -->
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-10 md:mb-14 pace-fade-up">
      <p class="text-sm tracking-wide text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-6 font-mono uppercase">
        Pace · v1 · for macOS
      </p>

      <h1 class="pace-headline-display text-white">
        I got tired of <span class="accent">Siri.</span>
        <br />
        So I made one that <span class="accent">stays on my Mac.</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-8 md:mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-10 items-end">
        <p class="pace-prose md:col-span-2 text-base md:text-lg">
          Pace is a voice assistant for macOS. Hold ctrl+option, say something,
          let go. It listens with your Mac's mic, reads your screen with a
          vision model on the same Apple Silicon chip, and clicks things
          for you. First answer in <strong>420 ms</strong>. No accounts.
          No cloud. <strong>$29 once.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="pace-margin-note text-right md:text-left md:pl-2 md:border-l md:border-[var(--color-border-subtle)]">
          The whole point is that <em>nothing leaves your Mac.</em><br />
          Including the bit where I tell you it doesn't.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE desktop. Wrapped in a rounded chrome that mirrors what
         the user is actually about to install. -->
    <div class="pace-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 120ms">
      <div class="pace-mac-shell relative mx-auto" role="img"
           aria-label="Animated demo of Pace running inside macOS: user speaks via push-to-talk, Pace thinks, Pace opens an app">

        <!-- Outer Mac chassis bezel -->
        <div class="pace-mac-bezel">

          <!-- ===== macOS menu bar (with Pace notch capsule centered) ===== -->
          <div class="pace-mac-menubar">
            <!-- Left: app menus -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-[12px] font-medium">
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[var(--color-accent)]">
                <span class="inline-flex items-end gap-[2px] h-3.5">
                  <span class="pace-bar h-2"></span>
                  <span class="pace-bar h-3.5"></span>
                  <span class="pace-bar h-2.5"></span>
                  <span class="pace-bar h-3"></span>
                </span>
                <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Pace</strong>
              </span>
              <span class="text-white/85">Safari</span>
              <span class="text-white/55">File</span>
              <span class="text-white/55">Edit</span>
              <span class="text-white/55">View</span>
              <span class="text-white/55">History</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Center: the Pace notch capsule itself -->
            <div class="pace-notch-capsule pace-capsule-listening-bg">
              <span class="inline-flex items-end gap-[2px] h-3.5 text-[var(--color-accent)]">
                <span class="pace-bar h-2"></span>
                <span class="pace-bar h-3.5"></span>
                <span class="pace-bar h-2.5"></span>
                <span class="pace-bar h-3"></span>
              </span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-white/70 tracking-wide uppercase font-medium">Listening</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Right: standard mac chrome -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[11px] text-white/70 font-medium">
              <span>🔋 92%</span>
              <span>◐</span>
              <span>📶</span>
              <span class="tabular-nums">9:41 AM</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- ===== Wallpaper / desktop surface ===== -->
          <div class="pace-desktop-surface">

            <!-- Safari window (foreground left) -->
            <div class="pace-window pace-window-safari">
              <div class="pace-window-titlebar">
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-close"></span>
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-min"></span>
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-zoom"></span>
                <span class="pace-window-url">news.ycombinator.com</span>
              </div>
              <div class="pace-window-body">
                <div class="text-[10px] text-orange-400 font-bold mb-2">Hacker News</div>
                <div class="space-y-1.5 text-[11px]">
                  <div>1. <span class="text-white">Pace 1.0 — voice control for macOS, fully on-device</span></div>
                  <div class="text-white/40 pl-3 text-[10px]">412 points · 87 comments · 2h ago</div>
                  <div class="mt-2">2. <span class="text-white/80">Show HN: I built a Mac voice agent that runs Qwen3-4B locally</span></div>
                  <div class="text-white/40 pl-3 text-[10px]">301 points · 64 comments · 4h ago</div>
                  <div class="mt-2">3. <span class="text-white/80">Why on-device AI is finally good enough for daily use</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Notes window (background right) -->
            <div class="pace-window pace-window-notes">
              <div class="pace-window-titlebar">
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-close"></span>
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-min"></span>
                <span class="pace-traffic-light pace-light-zoom"></span>
                <span class="pace-window-title">Quarterly planning</span>
              </div>
              <div class="pace-window-body text-[11px]">
                <div class="text-white/90 font-semibold mb-2">Q3 priorities</div>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-white/70 list-none">
                  <li>· Ship pace-tuned planner</li>
                  <li>· Cut TTFSW under 350 ms</li>
                  <li>· Add Linear MCP server</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Pace cursor — the actual app's blue arrow -->
            <svg class="pace-cursor-overlay" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <defs>
                <linearGradient id="paceCursorGrad" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
                  <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#6b9fff" />
                  <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#3a73e8" />
                </linearGradient>
              </defs>
              <path
                d="M3 2 L3 18 L7 14 L10 21 L13 20 L10 13 L16 13 Z"
                fill="url(#paceCursorGrad)"
                stroke="#ffffff"
                stroke-width="0.8"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              />
            </svg>

            <!-- The plan-then-execute thought bubble.
                 Lines stream in across the 14s loop driven by the
                 pace-step-N keyframes in global.css. -->
            <div class="pace-thought-bubble">
              <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-end gap-[2px] h-3 text-[var(--color-accent)]">
                  <span class="pace-bar h-1.5"></span>
                  <span class="pace-bar h-3"></span>
                  <span class="pace-bar h-2"></span>
                </span>
                Pace turn · 420 ms
              </div>

              <!-- Step 1: the user transcript -->
              <div class="pace-stream-line" data-step="1">
                <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-1">You said</div>
                <div class="text-[13px] text-white leading-snug">
                  "open hacker news and pin it to the left half"
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Step 2-5: the <think> scratchpad -->
              <div class="mt-4 pl-3 border-l border-[var(--color-border-subtle)]">
                <div class="pace-stream-line text-[10px] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-1" data-step="2">
                  &lt;think&gt;
                </div>
                <div class="pace-stream-line text-[11px] font-mono text-white/85 leading-relaxed" data-step="3">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">intent:</span>
                  open Hacker News, snap window left half.
                </div>
                <div class="pace-stream-line text-[11px] font-mono text-white/85 leading-relaxed" data-step="4">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">plan:</span>
                  open_url HN, then window snap-left.
                </div>
                <div class="pace-stream-line text-[11px] font-mono text-white/85 leading-relaxed" data-step="5">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">risk:</span>
                  none — reversible window placement.
                </div>
                <div class="pace-stream-line text-[10px] font-mono text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1" data-step="6">
                  &lt;/think&gt;
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Step 7: spoken response -->
              <div class="pace-stream-line mt-4" data-step="7">
                <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-1">Pace spoke</div>
                <div class="text-[13px] text-[var(--color-accent)] leading-snug">
                  Opening Hacker News and snapping it left.
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Step 8: tool call JSON. Braces are JSX-expression
                   markers in Astro templates so we wrap each opener
                   in a string expression to escape it. -->
              <div class="pace-stream-line mt-3" data-step="8">
                <div
                  class="font-mono text-[10.5px] text-white/80 bg-black/40 border border-[var(--color-border-subtle)] rounded-md px-2.5 py-2 leading-relaxed"
                >
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{'{'}"tool":</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)]">"open_url"</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">,"url":</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-positive)]">"news.ycombinator.com"</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{'}'}</span>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{'{'}"tool":</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)]">"window"</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">,"action":</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-positive)]">"snap_left"</span>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{'}'}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Step 9: the result -->
              <div class="pace-stream-line mt-3 flex items-center gap-2 text-[11px]" data-step="9">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-positive)]">✓</span>
                <span class="text-white/85">Done · 0 bytes sent off this Mac</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- PTT key chip — animated press during listening window -->
            <div class="pace-ptt-hint">
              <span class="pace-key-chip pace-key-chip-animated">⌃</span>
              <span class="text-white/50 text-xs">+</span>
              <span class="pace-key-chip pace-key-chip-animated">⌥</span>
              <span class="text-white/50 text-xs ml-2">hold to talk</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Dock -->
            <div class="pace-dock">
              <span title="Finder">📁</span>
              <span title="Safari" class="pace-dock-active">🧭</span>
              <span title="Mail">✉️</span>
              <span title="Calendar">📅</span>
              <span title="Notes">📝</span>
              <span title="Music">🎵</span>
              <span title="Messages">💬</span>
              <span title="Terminal">⌨️</span>
              <span title="Settings">⚙️</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTAs land BELOW the desktop. The visual sold the dream;
           the buttons close it. -->
      <div class="mt-12 md:mt-14 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 pace-fade-up">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
          <a href="#pricing" class="pace-cta-primary text-base">
            Download Pace — $29
            <span aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
          </a>
          <a href="#what-it-does" class="pace-cta-secondary text-base">
            See what it does
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          Free with Apple Intelligence · One-time payment · No subscription
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Outer chrome — gives the desktop a "framed device" feel
     without leaning on a literal Mac bezel photo. */
  .pace-mac-shell {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: 22px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a1d22 0%, #0c0d10 100%);
    padding: 8px;
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04) inset,
      0 30px 80px -20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9),
      0 12px 40px -10px rgba(79, 139, 255, 0.18);
  }

  .pace-mac-bezel {
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #000;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }

  /* macOS-style menu bar */
  .pace-mac-menubar {
    height: 28px;
    padding: 0 14px;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85);
    backdrop-filter: saturate(180%) blur(10px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    position: relative;
  }

  /* The notch capsule — centered absolutely so menus + clock can
     flow naturally around it. */
  .pace-notch-capsule {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 0;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: var(--color-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    border-top: none;
    border-radius: 0 0 16px 16px;
    padding: 4px 14px 6px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  /* The "desktop wallpaper" — restrained dual gradient that hints
     at depth without resorting to mesh blobs. */
  .pace-desktop-surface {
    position: relative;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    background:
      radial-gradient(140% 100% at 50% 0%, #1e2a4a 0%, #0a0c14 60%, #000 100%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #0e1424 0%, #050608 100%);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* Macishly translucent window frames */
  .pace-window {
    position: absolute;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(20, 22, 28, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) inset,
      0 30px 60px -10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .pace-window-safari {
    top: 8%;
    left: 4%;
    width: 38%;
    height: 56%;
    transform: rotate(-1.2deg);
  }

  .pace-window-notes {
    top: 18%;
    right: 4%;
    width: 26%;
    height: 38%;
    transform: rotate(0.8deg);
    opacity: 0.92;
  }

  .pace-window-titlebar {
    height: 28px;
    padding: 0 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  }
  .pace-traffic-light {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .pace-light-close { background: #ff5f56; }
  .pace-light-min { background: #ffbd2e; }
  .pace-light-zoom { background: #27c93f; }
  .pace-window-url,
  .pace-window-title {
    margin-left: 10px;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .pace-window-body {
    padding: 12px 14px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
    font-size: 11px;
  }

  /* Pace cursor — drifts between the Safari window and the bubble
     so the eye traces the action. */
  @keyframes pace-cursor-drift {
    0%, 8% { transform: translate(38%, 22%) rotate(-12deg); opacity: 1; }
    12%, 18% { transform: translate(22%, 38%) rotate(-12deg); opacity: 1; }
    25%, 70% { transform: translate(54%, 56%) rotate(-12deg); opacity: 1; }
    78%, 100% { transform: translate(38%, 22%) rotate(-12deg); opacity: 1; }
  }
  .pace-cursor-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 4px 8px rgba(79, 139, 255, 0.5));
    animation: pace-cursor-drift 14s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  /* The big "plan-then-execute" turn bubble. Anchors bottom-right
     of the desktop so it doesn't fight with the windows for visual
     weight. */
  .pace-thought-bubble {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 14%;
    right: 5%;
    width: min(42%, 380px);
    background: rgba(11, 11, 13, 0.94);
    backdrop-filter: blur(22px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(79, 139, 255, 0.22);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05) inset,
      0 20px 60px -10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9),
      0 0 0 1px rgba(79, 139, 255, 0.08);
  }

  .pace-ptt-hint {
    position: absolute;
    top: 12px;
    left: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 5px 8px;
  }

  /* macOS-style dock */
  .pace-dock {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 14px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 8px 14px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 18px;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px -8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }
  .pace-dock-active {
    transform: translateY(-2px) scale(1.08);
  }

  /* Mobile responsiveness — under 640 px the windows get cramped,
     so we hide the Notes window + tighten the bubble. The hero is
     still recognisable as a Mac scene at phone width. */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .pace-mac-shell { padding: 5px; border-radius: 16px; }
    .pace-mac-menubar { height: 24px; padding: 0 8px; font-size: 10px; }
    .pace-notch-capsule { padding: 3px 10px 5px; }
    .pace-window-notes { display: none; }
    .pace-window-safari { width: 56%; transform: rotate(-1deg); }
    .pace-thought-bubble {
      width: 88%;
      right: 6%;
      left: 6%;
      bottom: 18%;
      padding: 12px 14px;
    }
    .pace-dock { gap: 7px; font-size: 16px; padding: 6px 10px; }
    .pace-ptt-hint { top: 8px; left: 8px; padding: 3px 6px; }
  }
</style>
